<h2>CI integration</h2>

<p>Percy automatically supports the following CI services:</p>

<img src="/images/cis.png">

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://travis-ci.org/">Travis CI</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://circleci.com/">Circle CI</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://jenkins-ci.org/">Jenkins CI</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://codeship.com/">Codeship</a></li>
</ul>

<p>
  The {{#link-to "docs.capybara"}}Percy::Capybara{{/link-to}} library and low-level {{#link-to "apidocs.client"}}Percy::Client{{/link-to}} automatically discover if they're running in one of these environments and read the current branch name, Git commit SHA, repository name, and GitHub Pull Request (if any).
</p>
<p>
  You can see the code for this in the <code><a href="https://github.com/percy/percy-client/blob/master/lib/percy/client/environment.rb">percy/client/environment.rb</a></code> file. If you don't see your favorite CI service in the above list, please <a href="mailto:team@percy.io">contact us</a> or send us a PR to add support to the environment file.
</p>

